The paper is about graph visualization, which is a topic in computer science that falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also uses deep generative models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and computer vision techniques (cs.CV), as well as machine learning and deep learning methods (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents a new approach to graph visualization that does not rely on manually-defined heuristics, which could be considered a topic in the subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.SI).
